@notjamesearl to be against censorship is one thing. I'm in favor of freedom of speech, and entertainment shouldn't pull punches if it's meant to be satire, comedy, parody or whatever. 
To use conservative values as a shield against every work of fiction that goes against one's personal tastes or beliefs is lame. Bashing and antagonizing every content featuring minorities, female and different genders in central roles, or storytelling that defies traditional tropes or simply deviates from them, is pathetic.
AND, funny enough, is a form of censorship, and a political statement. Which makes all these "keep politics out of my media" guys a bunch of hypocrites.

@ComposedSage75 many of those fans bitching and whining are clueless and don't even know their own beloved franchises.
For instance the more I talk to Star Wars "fans", the more I discover how ignorant they are about the history of the franchise, the mythology behind the stories, and the philosophy behind Lucas' ideas.
Lucasfilm may have been a mixed bag in the last few years, but goddamn the majority of criticism coming from fans is just plain dumb.

